28/06/2004
SPLIT, Croatia -- The US guided missile destroyer USS Ramage arrived Sunday (27 June) at the port of Split for a joint exercise that begins Tuesday, as part of NATO's Partnership for Peace programme.
While in Split, members of the crew will meet with Croatian Navy Fleet Commander Commodore Ivica Tolic and local government officials.
In other news, train service resumed Saturday between Belgrade and Split, for the first time in 14 years.
Under the terms of an agreement between Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro, the train is to travel every Saturday until 4 September.
(HINA, HRT - 27/06/04;
HINA, B92 - 26/06/04)
